Uppermost Cenomanian to basal middle Turonian (lower Upper Cretaceous) strata are exposed in the Vallecillo quarry area. The holotype and only known specimen of Aquilolamnamilarcae (INAH 2544 P.F.17) comes from the Vallecillo Member of the Agua Nueva Formation, Pseudaspidoceras flexuosum Zone, lower Turonian (
) ( 32 ). The stratigraphic position of the specimen is indicated by the presence of the same slab of Pseudaspidoceras pseudonodosoides (
), an ammonite species which occurs only in the middle -upper Pseudaspidocerasflexuosum Zone at Vallecillo ( 33 ).

